gold bearing material, 5 vehicles and several mining equipment including two
generators, mining drill machines, camping tents, industrial hammers and a sieve
valued at about R500 000-00,"said MalulekeAll suspects will be processed to ascertain their correct
identity.He said the suspects are expected to appear before Giyani
Magistrate’s Court today for contravention of Section 5 (4) (a) (b) and (c)
read with Sec 1  of 98 (a) (1) and 99 (1)
(a) of the Mineral Resources Development Act 28 of 2002 and also read with Sec
332 of the Criminal Procedure Act 51 of 1977 and possession of gold bearing
material.Maluleke said Hawks have promised to continue with the
operations to prevent the looting of mineral resources from Giyani, and from other
districts in the province.